body_html:
So here is what happened: somehow, something installed a kernelspec for Jupyter in /usr/local/share/jupyter/kernels for my old python3.4 installation. I deleted the Kernelspec there, and Jupyter and the import of tf.nn.conv3d started working.

Sorry for the inconvenience.

So here is what happened: somehow, something installed a kernelspec for Jupyter in /usr/local/share/jupyter/kernels for my old python3.4 installation. I deleted the Kernelspec there, and Jupyter and the import of tf.nn.conv3d started working.

Sorry for the inconvenience.
